<TITLE> Dhaka stocks bounce back </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 30 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka stocks bounced in midday trade Monday after ending lower Sunday after a Securities and Exchange Commission move to make the merchant banks report credit ratios and prudential guidelines. The SEC Sunday directed merchant banks to send report on what ratio they extended loans to their clients. The regulator also asked them to submit prudential guidelines they follow in two days. The market traded higher from morning to midday amid a rush to buy shares with lower market capitalization. Insurance, pharmaceuticals and banking stocks traded upbeat. The DGEN or general index rallied 40.65 points or 1.70 percent to reach 2431.14 at 12:27pm. The DSI or all-share price index added 31.91 points or 1.65 percent to 1965.48. Of the issues traded, 139 advanced, 37 fell and 18 issues held steady. Turnover stood at Tk 1.12 billion. Total turnover was Tk 1.93 billion Tuesday. Square Pharma, UCBL and Southeast Bank ruled the turnover board until12:27pm. National Bank and Prime Bank were behind Southeast Bank. Square Pharma moved up to Tk 5464 from Sunday's close at Tk 5407.25. UCBL rose to Tk 3499.75 from Tk 3332.25. Southeast Bank advanced to Tk 585 from Tk 568.75. National Bank rose to Tk 1016.5 from Tk 968.25. Prime Bank was Tk 799.75 from Tk 763.75. Grameen1 Mutual Fund, AB Bank, Pubali Bank and Aims 1st Mutual Fund traded higher among the remaining top issues on turnover. Eastern Bank traded slightly lower due to profit-taking. bd
